   ```java
   private CompletableFuture<Optional<HubPrices>> fetchJitaPricesForType(int typeId, int jitaRegionId) {
       return esiClient.market.getRegionOrdersForType(jitaRegionId, "all", typeId)
           .thenApply(orders -> {
               if (orders.isEmpty()) return Optional.empty();

               double jitaBuy = orders.stream()
                   .filter(RegionOrder::isBuyOrder)
                   .mapToDouble(RegionOrder::price)
                   .max()
                   .orElse(0);

               double jitaSell = orders.stream()
                   .filter(o -> !o.isBuyOrder())
                   .mapToDouble(RegionOrder::price)
                   .min()
                   .orElse(0);

               return Optional.of(new HubPrices(jitaBuy, jitaSell));
           });
   }
   ```

2. **Update `getPublicContractItems()` to use live data:**
   ```java
   public CompletableFuture<List<ContractItemInfo>> getPublicContractItems(long contractId) {
       return CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> {
           var items = esiClient.contracts.getPublicContractItems(contractId).join();
           List<CompletableFuture<ContractItemInfo>> futures = items.stream()
               .map(item -> {
                   String typeName = typeCacheRepo.findNameById(item.typeId()).orElse("Type #" + item.typeId());

                   // First try cache (faster)
                   var cachedPrice = stationPriceRepo.findById(item.typeId(), Constants.JITA);
                   if (cachedPrice.isPresent()) {
                       return CompletableFuture.completedFuture(
                           new ContractItemInfo(item.typeId(), typeName, item.quantity(), 
                               item.isIncluded(), cachedPrice.get().buyPrice(), 
                               cachedPrice.get().sellPrice())
                       );
                   }

                   // Fallback to ESI (slower but always works)
                   return fetchJitaPricesForType(item.typeId(), Constants.JITA_REGION_ID)
                       .thenApply(prices -> new ContractItemInfo(item.typeId(), typeName, 
                           item.quantity(), item.isIncluded(),
                           prices.map(p -> p.jitaBuy()).orElse(0),
                           prices.map(p -> p.jitaSell()).orElse(0)));
               })
               .toList();

           return CompletableFuture.allOf(futures.toArray(new CompletableFuture[0]))
               .thenApply(v -> futures.stream().map(CompletableFuture::join).toList())
               .join();
       });
   }
   ```

3. **Add Jita region constant** (Constants.java):
   ```java
   public static final int JITA_REGION_ID = 10000002;  // The Forge
   ```

**Advantages:**
- Prices always available (no need for prior scan)
- Matches C# behavior of showing Jita prices on demand
- Leverages existing `getRegionOrdersForType()` ESI endpoint (line 47 in MarketApi.java)
- Can cache results in `StationPriceRepository` for future use (like C# does)
- Falls back to cache if available (hybrid approach)

**Performance Note:** The ESI endpoint `/v1/markets/{regionId}/orders/?order_type=all&type_id={typeId}` returns paginated results but typically just 1-2 pages for a single type.

